goals.question: What is the correlation between deaths and year?

```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.sort_values(by='Year')
    sns.lineplot(x='Year', y='Deaths', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the trend of deaths over the years?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.barplot(x="Entity", y="Deaths", data=data, ax=ax)
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    plt.title("What is the distribution of deaths across different entities?", wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['Year'])]
    data['Year'] = data['Year'].dt.strftime('%Y')
    avg_deaths = data['Deaths'].mean()
    ax = sns.lineplot(x='Year', y='Deaths', data=data)
    ax.axhline(avg_deaths, color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Average Deaths: {avg_deaths:.2f}')
    ax.set_title('What is the average number of deaths per year?')
    ax.set_xlabel('Year')
    ax.set_ylabel('Deaths')
    ax.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Deaths_pct_change'] = data['Deaths'].pct_change() * 100
    sns.lineplot(x='Year', y='Deaths_pct_change', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the percentage change in deaths between consecutive years?', wrap=True)
    plt.axhline(y=data['Deaths_pct_change'].median(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Median')
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
